&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox and Internet Explorer Users:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Recent updates in Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox and Internet Explorer now block mixed content by default, resulting in some content in ANGEL appearing as a broken link or not appearing at all.&lt;br /&gt;
Many users do not notice this default setting change at the time of the update and this can result in possible confusion during their ANGEL experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This issue is not specific to ANGEL and is browser-based. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solutions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(128, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Google Chrome Users :&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;If a user visits an HTTPS page with Mixed Active Content, they will see the following in the location bar: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;465&quot; height=&quot;65&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;$ENTRY_PATH$Untitled.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Clicking on the shield, they will see:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img width=&quot;411&quot; height=&quot;136&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;$ENTRY_PATH$2.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click on &amp;quot;Load unsafe script&amp;quot; &lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;link. All mixed content will load on the HTTPS page.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(128, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Firefox Users:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;If a user visits an HTTPS page with Mixed Active Content, they will see the following in the location bar: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://people.mozilla.com/%7Etvyas/FigureA.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;643&quot; height=&quot;86&quot; src=&quot;https://people.mozilla.com/%7Etvyas/FigureA.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Shield Icon Doorhanger shown on HTTPS page with Mixed Active Content&quot; class=&quot;aligncenter&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id=&quot;magicdomid56&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Clicking on the shield, they will see options to Learn More, Keep Blocking, or Disable Protection on This Page:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://people.mozilla.com/%7Etvyas/FigureB.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;637&quot; height=&quot;309&quot; src=&quot;https://people.mozilla.com/%7Etvyas/FigureB.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Shield Doorhanger Drop Down UI&quot; class=&quot;aligncenter&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Choose &amp;ldquo;Disable  Protection on This Page&amp;rdquo; - All mixed content will load on the HTTPS page  and the Lock icon will be replaced with a Yellow Warning Triangle:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;magicdomid63&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://people.mozilla.com/%7Etvyas/FigureD.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;644&quot; height=&quot;87&quot; src=&quot;https://people.mozilla.com/%7Etvyas/FigureD.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Yellow Warning Triangle appears after the user Disables Protection&quot; class=&quot; aligncenter&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(128, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internet Explorer Users: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;If a user visits an HTTPS page with Mixed Active Content, they will see the following in the bottom of their browser: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;960&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;$ENTRY_PATH$IE.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clicking on the &amp;quot;Show all content&amp;quot; button - &lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;All mixed content will load on the HTTPS page.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
